## 4. Interface Contract (Critical — Both People Must Agree)

This is the exact contract between UI and MCP server. Neither side deviates from this.

### REST API (UI → Backend)

#### `GET /api/schema`
Returns the full field schema so UI can dynamically build the onboarding form.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "sections": [
    {
      "section": "identity",
      "label": "About You",
      "fields": [
        {
          "field_key": "full_name",
          "label": "Full Name",
          "description": "Your legal or preferred name",
          "data_type": "text",
          "required": true,
          "sort_order": 1
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

#### `POST /api/profile`
Upserts one or more profile fields.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "fields": [
    {
      "section": "identity",
      "field_key": "full_name",
      "field_value": "Harish Kumar",
      "source": "manual"
    }
  ]
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{ "success": true, "updated": 1 }
```

#### `GET /api/profile`
Returns the full approved profile.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "profile": {
    "identity": {
      "full_name": "Harish Kumar",
      "location_city": "Portland"
    },
    "professional": {
      "job_title": "Entrepreneur",
      "company": "BespokeTales"
    }
  },
  "last_updated": "2025-03-28T10:00:00Z"
}
```

#### `GET /api/profile/{section}`
Returns one section only. Same shape as above but scoped.

#### `GET /api/health`
Returns `{ "status": "ok" }` — for UI to check server is running.

---

### MCP Tools (Agent → MCP Server)

These are the tools Claude or any agent calls via MCP (stdio transport).

#### Tool: `get_profile_section`
```json
{
  "name": "get_profile_section",
  "description": "Retrieve a specific section of the user's personal profile",
  "inputSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "section": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": ["identity", "professional", "preferences", "goals", "context"],
        "description": "The profile section to retrieve"
      }
    },
    "required": ["section"]
  }
}
```

**Returns:** JSON object of key-value pairs for that section.

#### Tool: `get_full_profile`
```json
{
  "name": "get_full_profile",
  "description": "Retrieve the user's complete personal profile across all sections",
  "inputSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Returns:** Full profile JSON (same shape as `GET /api/profile`).

#### Tool: `search_profile`
```json
{
  "name": "search_profile",
  "description": "Search the user's profile for fields matching a keyword",
  "inputSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "query": {
        "type": "string",
        "description": "Keyword to search across field keys and values"
      }
    },
    "required": ["query"]
  }
}
```

**Returns:** Array of matching `{section, field_key, field_value}` objects.

#### MCP Resource: `profile://schema`
Exposes the full field schema as an MCP resource — this is how the UI discovers what fields to show in the form.

```
URI: profile://schema
MIME type: application/json
Content: Same JSON as GET /api/schema
```

