## 8. Integration Points (How They Connect)

### CORS — Server must allow UI origin
Add to `main.py`:
```python
from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware

app.add_middleware(
    CORSMiddleware,
    allow_origins=["http://localhost:5173"],  # Vite dev server
    allow_methods=["*"],
    allow_headers=["*"],
)
```

### API base URL — UI hardcodes server address
In `ui/src/api.js`:
```javascript
const BASE = "http://localhost:8000";

export async function getSchema() {
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE}/api/schema`);
  return res.json();
}

export async function getProfile() {
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE}/api/profile`);
  return res.json();
}

export async function saveFields(fields) {
  const res = await fetch(`${BASE}/api/profile`, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    body: JSON.stringify({ fields })
  });
  return res.json();
}
```

### Health check — UI shows server status
On app load, UI calls `GET /api/health`. If it fails, show a banner: "MCP Server offline — start server first."

